                    "full_private_diary": [
                        "[S1901M] I secured an understanding with France: mutual non\u2011aggression at sea for S1901 (France will not contest the English Channel or North Sea; I will not threaten Brest). I warned Germany that any German fleet movement into the North Sea/Denmark will be treated as hostile; Germany replied with cautious neutrality (no firm promise). Russia signalled willingness to avoid Scandinavia and to pressure Germany on land rather than sea. Italy, Austria and Turkey remain noncommittal. No binding commitments were made beyond the Anglo\u2011French channel pact; Germany's posture remains the principal risk to the northern sealanes.\nIntent: S1901M orders I intend to give and will fulfill: F LON -> ENG (occupy Channel to secure sealanes); F EDI -> NTH (project naval presence into North Sea); A LVP -> YOR (secure northern coast and flexible access to Scotland or Yorkshire). I will honour the non\u2011aggression understanding with France; if Germany moves a fleet into NTH/DEN contrary to our talk, I will immediately shift to defensive posture in the North Sea and seek support from France and Russia.",
